Note:
Unit tests for compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/chacha20_poly1305.runa.

Test vectors:
  RFC 8439 section 2.8.2 (ChaCha20-Poly1305 AEAD example):
    Key: 80 81 82 83 84 85 86 87 88 89 8a 8b 8c 8d 8e 8f
         90 91 92 93 94 95 96 97 98 99 9a 9b 9c 9d 9e 9f
    Nonce: 07 00 00 00 40 41 42 43 44 45 46 47
    AAD: 50 51 52 53 c0 c1 c2 c3 c4 c5 c6 c7
    Plaintext: "Ladies and Gentlemen of the class of '99: If I could offer
                you only one tip for the future, sunscreen would be it."
    Ciphertext bytes 0..7: d3 1a 8d 34 64 8e 60 db
    Ciphertext bytes 110..113: 87 4d
    Tag: 1a:e1:0b:59:4f:09:e2:6a:7e:90:2e:cb:d0:60:06:91

Plus seal/open round-trip tests:
  - seal then open with the same params yields the original plaintext.
  - open with a mutated tag returns 0.
  - open with mutated ciphertext returns 0.
  - open with mutated AAD returns 0.
:End Note

Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as T
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/chacha20_poly1305.runa" as AEAD

Process called "compare_bytes" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ba be Memory.memory_get_byte(a, i)
        Let bb be Memory.memory_get_byte(b, i)
        If ba is not equal to bb:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

